			<sawd:htmlView name="HTML 1" duid="0oaouic28aft8dk3">
				<sawd:HTML fmt="html" captionID="kcap12832459_480">&lt;font color=darkblue&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Description :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; This page showcases the following prompting capability on a hierarchical column.[br/]
[b]Slider[/b] - This feature adds slider as a new prompting control. They can be used with numeric data for easy analysis. The range slider can be used with the &quot;is Between&quot; operator for changing the boundary values.[br/]
[b]Qualified data reference (QDR)[/b] - A QDR is a qualifier that limits one or more of the dimensions to retrieve a single value for a measure column. Using this feature, you can qualify which value to use for a condition evaluation.When defining a prompt, it might be necessary to &#39;pin&#39; or qualify which member value from another dimension should be used to evaluate a condition. The QDR is the mechanism to do that.[br/]
[b]Variable[/b] - This feature adds the ability to set a variable with a prompt selection. This allows the user to define prompts for values that are not associated to a column.
</sawd:HTML>
			</sawd:htmlView>
			
			<sawd:htmlView name="HTML 3" duid="0oaouic28aft8dk3">
				<sawd:HTML fmt="html" captionID="kcap12832459_482">&lt;font color=darkblue&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Setup :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Choice List user input options on hierarchy columns can be created as any other dashboard prompt by using New -&gt; Dashboard Prompt. Once within the prompt definition dialog, select Column Prompt -&gt; Hierarchy Column. The Choice List option is the only user input option for a hierarchical prompt.[br/]

[b]Slider[/b] can be created as any other dashboard prompt by using New-&gt;Dashboard Prompt-&gt;Column Prompt (User Input = Slider).[br/]
[b]QDRs[/b] are defined within the member selection step in the Answers Analysis editor. They can be found under the For section of the step definition.[br/]

[b]Variable[/b] prompts can be created as any other dashboard prompt by using New-&gt;Dashboard Prompt-&gt; Variable Prompt.[br/]</sawd:HTML>
			</sawd:htmlView>
